                  </persName>
             is my brother; he is a carver and gilder, and lives in Frith-street, Soho - on the 21st of June, the prisoner came to me and brought this note; I told him he was not in my brother's service, and the note was not my brother's writing - I know the prisoner; he had been in my brother's service, and knew my brother dealt with me, but he had left him for nearly three years - he said he had been away for some time, but he had returned to my brother the last Monday, and he said the note was written and given to him by my brother - I sent for an officer - this is the note he brought.(read.)</p>
               <p>Dear Brother, - Will you oblige me with the loan of 3 sovereigns, as I have a bill come due, and I want to take up by half-past one o'clock. I have not sufficient in the house. Please to send by bearer immediately. - Yours, - JOHN COLLYER.</p>
